Classes in com.android.slackandhay.gameobject.component used by com.android.slackandhay.gameobject.component
GOComponent
           Components are what makes gameObjects functional: as the constituting parts of their parent object, they can add properties, behavior or certain services to it.
GOComponentControl
          this class represents how game objects are controlled, meaning right now that they be controlled via an AI or the hardware controls (like the touch screen) The ComponentAI and the ComponentInput inherit this class
GOComponentDefense
          A component of this type handles damage that is dealt by other gameObjects, which means it literally decided what to do with it.
GOComponentGraphics
          This Component lets game objects be rendered on the screen
GOComponentHealth
          This type of component represents the idea that there is a certain amount of damage a gameObject can take before it will be considered 'dead' or 'destroyed'.
GOComponentMovement
          A component of this type implements movement on a macro level, that is, it can be given a target point in world coordinates and it will do its best (which can amount to as little or as much as the implementation cares) to get there.
GOComponentMovement.DirectionFinder
           
GOComponentOffense
          A component of this type is able to deal damage to other gameObjects.
GOComponentSound
          This component is used to generate sounds for the game objects
GOComponentSpatial
          This component provides a location and an orientation in space, which is currently limited to two dimensions.
